1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,440
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 2]

23
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,040
[Move this image to the Recycle Bin?
Cancel / Move to Recycle Bin]

24
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,730
Excuse me, officer.

25
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,170
Here's the thing.

26
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,170
I've been under the weather lately,

27
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:08,650
so I brought some
traditional Chinese medicine with me.

28
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:09,530
But

29
00:02:09,760 --> 00:02:11,410
I just saw a notice saying

30
00:02:11,430 --> 00:02:13,250
valuable herbs can't be taken
out of the country.

31
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,900
Now I'm not sure about mine.

32
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,130
Could you please take a look?

33
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:19,530
Sure. Follow me, please.

34
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,690
Just a moment, please.

35
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:27,970
Shihuo.

36
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,690
This gentleman says
he's carrying some herbs.

37
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,090
Could you take a look?

38
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:32,620
Sure.

39
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:39,970
- Hello. - Please open it yourself.

40
00:02:39,990 --> 00:02:40,500
Okay.

41
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:47,850
There are Solomon's seal, dendrobium,

42
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,460
and dried snake in here.

43
00:02:53,990 --> 00:02:56,530
Your herbs have been processed
and ground for decoction

44
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:57,340
as prescribed.

45
00:02:57,390 --> 00:02:59,060
The quantity
is within personal-use limits.

46
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,020
So you may take them abroad.

47
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:00,620
Okay.

48
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:01,340
But

49
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:03,530
if your destination country
has restrictions,

50
00:03:03,670 --> 00:03:05,500
you may not get
through customs there.

51
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,900
Got it.

52
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,780
Thank you.

53
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:15,780
Shihuo,

54
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,250
I still think something's off about him.

55
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:18,940
Thanks.

56
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,570
Sir,

57
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,620
please put it
through the X-ray machine again.

58
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,690
Sure. Thanks.

59
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,370
Hello, sir.

60
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,090
Is this bag yours, too?

61
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:34,130
Yes.

62
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:36,020
We need to check it as well.

63
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,650
No problem.

64
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,180
Happy to cooperate.

65
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,530
Zhang Yu, you do it.

66
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:42,300
Me?

67
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,180
Please, go ahead.

68
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:58,300
Electric toothbrush.

69
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:10,180
Binoculars.

70
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:31,740
It's okay. I'll do it.

71
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:44,010
I'm sorry

72
00:04:44,030 --> 00:04:45,210
for all the trouble.

73
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:45,890
Thanks.

74
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:46,810
Sorry.

75
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:49,130
We need to put this bag
through the X-ray, too.

76
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,500
Okay.

77
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:05,100
There's something suspicious.

78
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,010
It's not clear.

79
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:13,620
Also,

80
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,570
we need you

81
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:16,980
to take off your suit.

82
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:37,660
Here. Search it!
What else do you want to check?

83
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:38,940
Please wait a moment.

84
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:42,890
Ma'am,

85
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,810
I came to you for help on my own.

86
00:05:46,470 --> 00:05:48,250
I've cooperated with every check.

87
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:50,010
If you keep stalling for time

88
00:05:50,030 --> 00:05:50,980
and making it difficult for me,

89
00:05:51,270 --> 00:05:52,250
I'll file a complaint.

90
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,130
We're not stalling for me.

91
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,570
Really?

92
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:57,690
Then what?

93
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,770
Bored?

94
00:06:00,350 --> 00:06:01,210
Got nothing better to do?

95
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:03,060
Just messing with me?

96
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:09,370
No private filming
in the inspection area.

97
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,010
Please put your phones away.

98
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:11,450
Alright?

99
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:12,890
Hey, why can't we film?

100
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:14,450
We're citizens!

101
00:06:14,470 --> 00:06:15,980
We have the right
to oversee law enforcement.

102
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:16,770
Why can't we film?

103
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,810
Come on, everyone, record this!

104
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:22,890
First the suitcase, then the backpack,

105
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:25,100
now the suit!

106
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:27,330
What have you even found?

107
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,980
Someone record this and post it online!

108
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,370
Let everyone see

109
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:34,570
how officials bully ordinary folks!

110
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,450
Sir,

111
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,330
hello.

112
00:06:37,710 --> 00:06:39,330
I'm the director
of Passenger Inspection Section I

113
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:40,540
at Huayan Airport Customs.

114
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:41,740
Please calm down.

115
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,130
Let me find out what's going on.

116
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:44,300
What's going on?

117
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,500
I think there's something off
about this gentleman.

118
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,250
Do you have any evidence?

119
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:53,980
I…

120
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,300
Not yet.

121
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:58,570
Can you just detain someone
without any evidence?

122
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:00,010
Apologize to him.

123
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,330
Mr. Guo…

124
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:02,130
Apologize.

125
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,060
And write me a self-criticism
by tomorrow.

126
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:06,210
Alright, sir.

127
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:07,770
No need to apologize.

128
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:09,330
Since she's new,

129
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:10,740
a small mistake

130
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:11,980
is understandable.

131
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:12,860
I'm in a hurry.

132
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,250
Sorry, sir,

133
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,770
for the unpleasant experience.

134
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:17,660
Here, give me your thermos.

135
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,940
I'll top it up for you.

136
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:20,690
Thermos?

137
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,370
When your bag went through the X-ray,

138
00:07:23,390 --> 00:07:25,060
I saw a thermos in there.

139
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,330
Don't bother.

140
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:28,210
Sir.

141
00:07:28,230 --> 00:07:30,010
It's no trouble.
It's the least we can do.

142
00:07:30,030 --> 00:07:30,810
Let me have it.

143
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,770
I have a flight to catch.
I'm in a hurry.

144
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:35,210
No rush.
I'm just getting you some warm water.

145
00:07:35,350 --> 00:07:36,540
It won't take long.

146
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,740
I just feel bad
for causing you more trouble.

147
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,570
Not at all.

148
00:07:42,710 --> 00:07:43,980
My flight's about to leave,
so let's forget it.

149
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,740
It's fine.

150
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:45,540
Dayu.

151
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,180
Dayu, hurry up!

152
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:47,980
Coming.

153
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,300
Warm water is good.

154
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,890
Helps keep you healthy, right?

155
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,250
It's almost empty.

156
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,420
You're into goji berries, too?

157
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,010
Well, I'm middle-aged now.

158
00:07:57,030 --> 00:07:58,130
Yeah, same here.

159
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,250
How much water did you boil?

160
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,740
About a bottle of mineral water.

161
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:04,740
A bottle?

162
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:08,330
Your thermos is all show.

163
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:09,890
Big on the outside, tiny on the inside.

164
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,330
That's why I picked it.

165
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:12,500
Thick walls. Good insulation.

166
00:08:13,350 --> 00:08:14,060
Let go.

167
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,660
I said let go!

168
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,210
Genetic sample container?

169
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,660
Sir,

170
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:31,940
you know exactly

171
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:33,570
what this is, don't you?

172
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,570
Shihuo.

173
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:36,420
Send it for testing.

174
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:36,850
Okay.

175
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:39,140
Sir,

176
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,690
please come with me.

177
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,210
Deng, notify the anti-smuggling unit.

178
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:48,940
Got it.

179
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,610
Good job, Zhang.

180
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,570
Have a seat.

181
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:02,730
You have zero field experience,

182
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,540
but he still didn't manage
to slip one past you.

183
00:09:04,590 --> 00:09:05,690
Slip one past me?

184
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:07,970
Like what he just did.

185
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,780
He deliberately kept hovering
right under your nose

186
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,060
so you'd let your guard down.

187
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:15,610
Mr. Guo.

188
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:18,260
Well, are the test results in yet?

189
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,900
Are the test results in yet?

190
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:21,850
Not that fast.

191
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,060
It'll take some more time.

192
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:27,210
Actually, when I had you apologize
to Qian Shengkai,

193
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:29,570
I was trying to keep him occupied.

194
00:09:29,990 --> 00:09:32,300
That said,
you were partly at fault, too.

195
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:34,020
What was I wrong about?

196
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:35,690
Passenger inspection

197
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,380
requires sharp instincts.

198
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,140
But you also need a strategy.

199
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:42,450
You have to learn to play along

200
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:43,450
and shift focus.

201
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,380
Just like what Qian did.

202
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,140
He got you focused

203
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,420
on his backpack

204
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,540
and suitcase

205
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:51,810
so you'd overlook
the thermos in his hand.

206
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,300
Then he ramped up the confrontation.

207
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,780
That threw you off even more.

208
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,420
Right?

209
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:57,810
Yes.

210
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:00,330
Cong,

211
00:10:00,990 --> 00:10:03,450
Zhang's been on the job
for less than 24 hours.

212
00:10:03,590 --> 00:10:04,850
She's already doing great.

213
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:07,660
Right? Be patient.

214
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:10,060
Think about how your mentor
taught you back then.

215
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:14,300
I may still be new
to passenger inspection,

216
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:15,690
but I believe

217
00:10:15,710 --> 00:10:17,660
I'll grow into the job.

218
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,140
New to the job…

219
00:10:23,710 --> 00:10:24,730
Grow into it…

220
00:10:25,990 --> 00:10:26,810
What is it?

221
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:29,570
You searched Qian's belongings

222
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:31,300
and found nothing unusual.

223
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:32,570
So why didn't you let him go?

224
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:33,490
I…

225
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,780
I just had a feeling.

226
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,490
Talk me through it.

227
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:40,140
Excuse me, officer.

228
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:42,450
I've been under the weather lately,

229
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:44,300
so I brought some
traditional Chinese medicine with me.

230
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:48,140
There are Solomon's seal, dendrobium…

231
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,260
Electric toothbrush.

232
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,060
Binoculars.

233
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,730
- Too new. - Too new.

234
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:07,020
His suit was almost spotless.

235
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,210
His suitcase and backpack
showed no signs of use.

236
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:10,180
And the clothes,

237
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,940
toothbrush, electric razor,
and hair dryer inside

238
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,300
were almost unpacked.

239
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,380
Deng, take everyone to the duty room

240
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,300
and wait for me there.

241
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,180
You come with me.

242
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:21,940
Mr. Shen,

243
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,850
I request that Flight ADF331 be delayed.

244
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,970
The genetic sample container
is likely on board.

245
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:28,610
Guo Cong,

246
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:30,260
what exactly did you promise me
last night?

247
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,660
I'm only 50 percent sure.

248
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:33,810
But my mentor said
one mistake can cost everything.

249
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:35,180
So please help me.

250
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,940
This kid's ordering me around now.

251
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,570
Ladies and gentlemen,

252
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:43,450
welcome aboard.

253
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:45,540
This is your purser speaking.

254
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,810
We will be taking off shortly.

255
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:49,850
Please fasten your seat belts

256
00:11:49,990 --> 00:11:51,180
and ensure your tray tables are stowed.

257
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,180
Mr. Guo.

258
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,220
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
Pull up all the surveillance footage

259
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:57,450
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
and cue it to 7:50 AM.

260
00:11:57,470 --> 00:11:58,180
Got it.

261
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,380
Ordinary passengers
carry things that look used.

262
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,660
But Qian's were too new.

263
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,850
Even a rookie like you can see it.

264
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:25,380
The smuggling ring can see it, too.

265
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,810
So the fact that Qian Shengkai's stuff
is brand new

266
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:30,330
is the crack they left
for us on purpose.

267
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,380
They only have one goal.

268
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,330
To cover

269
00:12:32,350 --> 00:12:34,140
the real carrier
of the blood genetic sample.

270
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,970
Gene testing takes time.

271
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:40,660
Qian was just the bait to buy time.

272
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,570
He lured us into making a move

273
00:12:42,870 --> 00:12:43,970
so the real carrier

274
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,420
could get through behind him.

275
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:46,690
So

276
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,540
the real carrier must've come after him.

277
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:00,730
Guo Cong,

278
00:13:00,830 --> 00:13:01,810
you only have 15 minutes.

279
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:02,970
This is an international flight.

280
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,180
There are diplomatic personnel on board.

281
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,810
Without solid evidence,

282
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:07,970
the plane must take off at 8:50 AM.

283
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:09,330
We're very sorry.

284
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,730
What's going on?

285
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:20,680
[For 24 Only]

286
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,160
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

287
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:02,940
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
It's her.

288
00:14:07,590 --> 00:14:09,180
When Qian was taken away,

289
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,450
this woman glanced at him,

290
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:11,420
and the corner of her mouth

291
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,330
lifted slightly.

292
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:13,690
She had deliberately dressed

293
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:15,810
as plainly as possible to look ordinary.

294
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:17,540
But her high heels

295
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,970
didn't match
the rest of her outfit at all.

296
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,940
And she was putting more weight
on her left foot than her right.

297
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,900
So I suspect

298
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:25,260
there's a sample container hidden
in the heel of her right shoe.

299
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:26,380
Mr. Shen.

300
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,260
I'm requesting permission
to board Flight ADF331 for inspection.

301
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:30,570
How sure are you?

302
00:14:30,830 --> 00:14:31,780
Fifty percent.

303
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,810
She's 50 percent sure, too.

304
00:14:33,990 --> 00:14:35,330
So that's

305
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:36,570
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
twenty-five percent.

306
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,970
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
Who taught you math?

307
00:14:37,970 --> 00:14:38,920
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

308
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:39,570
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
Don't freeze up.

309
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:41,380
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
Now take Zhang Yu and board the plane.

310
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,490
But if you find nothing,

311
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:45,660
that's an unjustified delay.

312
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,730
You'll both write a formal statement,
and you may even be suspended.

313
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:50,260
I'll take responsibility.

314
00:14:50,510 --> 00:14:51,330
So will I.

315
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,260
Good. I'll coordinate with the airport
and the anti-smuggling unit.

316
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:53,690
Go on.

317
00:14:53,710 --> 00:14:54,210
Yes, sir.

318
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:56,280
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

319
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:56,730
Let's go.

320
00:14:58,920 --> 00:14:59,690
Hello?

321
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:01,780
Copy that.

322
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,260
Get your purser over here.

323
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:23,970
Quiet down!

324
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,450
Here comes your knight

325
00:15:25,470 --> 00:15:27,210
in shining armor.

326
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,020
Knock it off.

327
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,300
He must be here for something serious.

328
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,090
Everyone, quiet down!

329
00:15:31,110 --> 00:15:31,730
Quiet down.

330
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:32,660
Thank you. Quiet down.

331
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,450
Everybody, settle down.

332
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:38,540
Hello.

333
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,300
[China Customs Enforcement ID]
China Customs.

334
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:44,970
Me?

335
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:47,850
What do you mean?

336
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:49,490
What's going on?

337
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:52,780
Please take your luggage
and come with us.

338
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,090
What's this about?

339
00:15:55,110 --> 00:15:57,090
Why are you taking me off the plane?

340
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:57,780
Take her away.

341
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,540
What is this all about?

342
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,810
I'm filing a complaint.

343
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,900
What a hassle.

344
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,940
Why did you take me off the plane?

345
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:51,690
You've ruined my whole schedule!

346
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,730
I'm going to file a complaint!

347
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:56,210
This is absolutely ridiculous!

348
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:59,330
I was just carrying something
for a friend.

349
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:00,900
I need an explanation!

350
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,020
Ms. Shizuko Nishimura,

351
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:05,660
you carried contraband,

352
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:08,900
delayed the flight,

353
00:17:09,360 --> 00:17:12,820
and violated the rights
of other passengers.

354
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:16,660
More importantly,
you're suspected of smuggling.

355
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:20,250
That's against Chinese law.

356
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:25,820
The only thing you can do now
is cooperate

357
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:28,180
and tell us the truth.

358
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:52,450
Li, I'm sorry.

359
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,420
The package is lost.

360
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:56,660
The video is all over the internet.

361
00:18:03,030 --> 00:18:04,450
Recently, on a flight,

362
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:07,250
China Customs uncovered a case
involving a foreign traveler

363
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,970
attempting to smuggle genetic samples

364
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:10,290
out of the country.

365
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:12,100
Netizens have dubbed
one of the customs officers

366
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:14,860
China's Most Handsome Customs Officer.

367
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,180
Hello?

368
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,490
Dabao.

369
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,100
Go find out the information

370
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,290
about these two customs officers.

371
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:35,380
I'll talk to the client
about the shipment.

372
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,970
Anything money can fix

373
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,210
isn't really a problem.

374
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:41,580
Ziyi,

375
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,490
I'm out.

376
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:47,180
I can't believe you've been gone
three years already.

377
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:49,860
I know

378
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,490
you didn't drown
because you were drunk.

379
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,380
Your death

380
00:18:56,030 --> 00:18:57,290
has to be connected to that doll

381
00:18:57,310 --> 00:18:59,490
at the airport five years ago.

382
00:19:18,990 --> 00:19:20,450
Just wait for me.

383
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:23,620
I will find the person
who left that doll

384
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,860
and avenge you.

385
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,290
Nice work.

386
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,940
What other languages do you speak?

387
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,860
Mentor, I majored in English and French,

388
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,900
with a minor in Greek.

389
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,100
So you taught yourself Japanese?

390
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:56,380
I'm an anime fan.

391
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,490
And to study criminal psychology,

392
00:19:58,510 --> 00:20:00,690
I've read a lot of Japanese
henkaku mystery novels.

393
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:02,290
What did you just call me?

394
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:03,940
Mentor.

395
00:20:04,310 --> 00:20:05,290
Mr. Shen assigned you

396
00:20:05,310 --> 00:20:06,820
to be my mentor, right?

397
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:09,940
And today, in all that chaos,

398
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,770
you still managed to spot the smuggler.

399
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,770
You're my mentor, no question.

400
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,250
Spotting smugglers

401
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:17,380
is just part of our job
in passenger inspection.

402
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:20,580
Right, don't call me your mentor
in front of the others.

403
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,210
We'll talk about it later.

404
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:21,940
Got it?

405
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:24,010
Yes, Mr. Guo.

406
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:27,140
By the way, did you see
how Qian reacted just now?

407
00:20:29,230 --> 00:20:30,180
No.

408
00:20:30,310 --> 00:20:31,730
I was focused entirely

409
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:33,180
on Shizuko Nishimura.

410
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:35,290
I was worried
she might make a sudden move.

411
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,490
As a passenger inspection officer,

412
00:20:36,510 --> 00:20:38,450
you don't have to have eyes
in the back of your head.

413
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:39,730
But you should at least pay attention

414
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:41,050
to what's happening
right in front of you.

415
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:43,490
I'll keep that in mind next time.

416
00:20:44,070 --> 00:20:47,050
So what did you notice?

417
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:50,050
Shizuko Nishimura and Qian
don't know each other.

418
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,940
Each of them is in one-on-one contact
with their own handler.

419
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:53,820
Most importantly,

420
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:54,690
Qian Shengkai

421
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:56,490
has no idea he's just a decoy.

422
00:20:57,470 --> 00:20:59,660
This smuggling ring is way too cunning.

423
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:03,210
Have you ever dealt with an opponent

424
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:04,580
this calculating before?

425
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:09,290
Three years ago,
when my mentor was still here.

426
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:11,660
Then you must have taken them all down.

427
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:12,900
Tell me about it.

428
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:15,100
Another time.

429
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:17,660
By the way,

430
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:19,140
I have one more question.

431
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:21,900
What do we do with Qian Shengkai?

432
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,140
Just as predicted.

433
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:24,660
Test results came back clean.

434
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:25,690
But he's clearly

435
00:21:25,710 --> 00:21:27,290
a diversion of the smuggling ring.

436
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:28,530
That's just our theory.

437
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:29,530
Do you have proof?

438
00:21:29,550 --> 00:21:31,530
The thermos with the hidden compartment.

439
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,380
There was a sample container inside.

440
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,970
Taking a reagent box filled with herbs

441
00:21:34,990 --> 00:21:37,180
out of the country by hiding it
in a thermos with a compartment.

442
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,180
It's up to the authorities to decide

443
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,860
how that act should be classified.

444
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:42,970
Then

445
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:44,210
what about the leads behind him?

446
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:45,380
We're not going after them?

447
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,820
We're passenger inspection officers,

448
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:49,250
not detectives in your novels
who chase every lead to the very end.

449
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,860
Our job is to stop anything illegal

450
00:21:52,230 --> 00:21:54,140
from crossing the border

451
00:21:54,310 --> 00:21:55,420
right at the border.

452
00:21:56,070 --> 00:21:57,290
Focus on your job.

453
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:58,450
Got it?

454
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:00,250
Yes.

455
00:22:03,310 --> 00:22:04,660
So you're saying

456
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,770
I can handle
passenger inspection work now?

457
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,450
Acceptable so far.

458
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,340
China's Most Handsome Customs Officer.

459
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,820
Mr. Shen is looking for you.

460
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:16,770
Wait here for me. I'll be right back.

461
00:22:16,790 --> 00:22:17,210
Yes.

462
00:22:20,030 --> 00:22:20,970
Zhang Yu.

463
00:22:20,990 --> 00:22:22,050
Everyone in this room

464
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,530
has their eyes on you right now.

465
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:26,050
…China's Most Handsome Customs Officer.

466
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:26,620
Zhang Yu.

467
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:28,450
Everyone in this room

468
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:31,580
is fighting over who gets
to be your mentor.

469
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:34,010
Except Yan Bowen and me.

470
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,100
Count me out.

471
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:37,530
Lyu Xiaoyan

472
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,970
and my daughter are already enough.

473
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,770
I don't have the energy
to take on anyone else.

474
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:44,970
What are you saying, Mentor?

475
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:47,050
If nobody's assigned yet,

476
00:22:47,070 --> 00:22:49,820
learn from my mentor, Shihuo.
He's solid.

477
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,770
Forget Shihuo.

478
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:54,900
He's such a quiet one.

479
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,820
He won't say more than he has to.

480
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:58,820
You guys remember?

481
00:22:58,840 --> 00:23:00,180
Bowen used to be

482
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,580
so talkative when he first came.

483
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:03,340
Now he's picked up Shihuo's habits.

484
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,620
He's got plenty in his head

485
00:23:05,270 --> 00:23:06,250
but can't get any of it out.

486
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,970
The wise speak little, Dayu.

487
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,620
I

488
00:23:13,030 --> 00:23:14,620
have been in this section for years.

489
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,450
I may not be as senior as Deng,

490
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,770
but compared with Mr. Guo and Shihuo,

491
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:21,010
I'm no less experienced.

492
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:23,620
So why haven't I

493
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,100
had a single trainee all these years?

494
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,860
Only one reason.

495
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:29,140
Which is…

496
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:31,180
- No real talent has come along.
- No real talent.

497
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:33,180
Because you never shut up!

498
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:35,730
Deng!

499
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,210
Only Deng dares to tell the truth.

500
00:23:37,230 --> 00:23:38,210
Enough.

501
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,340
Stop messing around.

502
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:41,250
Yeah, I talk a lot.

503
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,530
That's just who I am.

504
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:44,290
I never hold anything back.

505
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,580
Don't worry, Zhang Yu.
If you become my trainee,

506
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,770
I'll pass on every bit of experience
and wisdom I've got,

507
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:50,380
- breaking it down… - Breaking it down.

508
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,050
You stole his line.

509
00:23:52,070 --> 00:23:52,860
…for you.

510
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,820
I'll teach you everything I know.

511
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,140
Save it.

512
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,620
She's already spoken for.

513
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:05,140
Thanks, everyone.

514
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:08,660
But actually,
Mr. Shen already assigned Mr. Guo

515
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,290
as my mentor.

516
00:24:10,550 --> 00:24:12,730
So you were his student

517
00:24:12,750 --> 00:24:14,860
before you became part of us.

518
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:18,420
Great. There goes my shot.

519
00:24:18,470 --> 00:24:20,050
An assignment's an assignment.

520
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:22,340
But Zhang Yu,

521
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,620
do you know why they put you
at the screening post

522
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,860
on your first day?

523
00:24:29,510 --> 00:24:31,940
Let me break it down for you.

524
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:35,250
I bet I'm the only one

525
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:37,250
in this room who…

526
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:39,100
Hey, why's everyone walking away?

527
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:42,140
It's fine. Let me finish.

528
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:44,770
I'm the only one here

529
00:24:44,790 --> 00:24:47,290
who gets what Guo Cong was really doing.

530
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:52,770
Handing a case this important
to a rookie.

531
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:54,770
Were you trying to scare her off?

532
00:24:55,470 --> 00:24:57,420
I know what's at stake.

533
00:24:57,470 --> 00:24:58,580
Why would I mess

534
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,580
with something this important?

535
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,450
You're a veteran in this line of work.

536
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:04,900
You know exactly what I was thinking.

537
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:05,970
How did you know

538
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:07,660
she could handle the pressure?

539
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,580
The fact is,

540
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:10,900
when it mattered, she did.

541
00:25:12,030 --> 00:25:13,690
I think Zhang Yu

542
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:14,900
is an interesting one.

543
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:16,050
Let me.

544
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:16,860
Just sit.

545
00:25:18,270 --> 00:25:19,380
Deep down,

546
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,420
she's got a stubborn streak.

547
00:25:20,510 --> 00:25:22,770
And her instincts are razor sharp.

548
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:25,490
I think she's made
for passenger inspection.

549
00:25:25,510 --> 00:25:26,490
Very promising.

550
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:28,490
Promising, right?

551
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:29,140
Yes.

552
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,820
Then train her well.

553
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:32,180
I'll do my best.

554
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:36,860
Mr. Shen.

555
00:25:38,750 --> 00:25:41,380
Don't you think the smugglers' methods

556
00:25:41,470 --> 00:25:43,420
this time feel familiar?

557
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:47,050
You mean Group E?

558
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:51,250
Since my mentor took down
Group E three years ago,

559
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:53,730
smuggling rings that can pull off
that many decoys

560
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:56,420
to cover their real operations

561
00:25:56,470 --> 00:25:57,450
have been gone.

562
00:25:57,550 --> 00:25:58,820
Now this one pops up.

563
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:01,490
I think Group E might be
making a comeback.

564
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:04,490
Don't jump to conclusions yet.

565
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,690
It's hard

566
00:26:06,710 --> 00:26:09,530
to link this one case to Group E.

567
00:26:10,710 --> 00:26:12,530
But one thing I can say for sure

568
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,140
is that this crew is cunning.

569
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:16,730
You all need to stay on full alert.

570
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:19,900
Yes, sir.

571
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:20,660
Go back to your work.

572
00:26:26,790 --> 00:26:28,210
So both the smugglers and we

573
00:26:28,230 --> 00:26:29,450
used the same

574
00:26:29,470 --> 00:26:31,010
bait-and-trap tactic.

575
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:31,900
But Zhang Yu,

576
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,140
you weren't the one setting the trap.

577
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,940
You were the bait.

578
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:41,180
Mr. Guo,

579
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:43,290
is Dayu telling the truth?

580
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,620
Was I just bait

581
00:26:46,030 --> 00:26:48,250
you threw to the smugglers?

582
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:51,530
Mr. Shen just talked to me.

583
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:53,660
I was just about
to walk everyone through it.

584
00:26:53,710 --> 00:26:54,530
Have a seat.

585
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,690
After we got the late-night notice
about the genetic sample case,

586
00:26:58,990 --> 00:27:00,050
one question kept bothering me.

587
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:01,970
The gold smuggling case

588
00:27:01,990 --> 00:27:03,530
and the blood genetic sample
smuggling case

589
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,580
both involved the same flight,

590
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,940
ADF331.

591
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:09,420
That was too much of a coincidence.

592
00:27:10,510 --> 00:27:11,530
I felt

593
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:12,690
there might be

594
00:27:12,710 --> 00:27:14,450
some connection

595
00:27:14,470 --> 00:27:15,620
between the two cases.

596
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:17,660
It is possible

597
00:27:17,990 --> 00:27:20,140
that the gold smuggling was a setup.

598
00:27:20,710 --> 00:27:21,900
A diversion

599
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,100
meant to distract and mislead us.

600
00:27:23,230 --> 00:27:24,820
Its only purpose

601
00:27:24,990 --> 00:27:27,420
was to cover the smuggling
of the blood genetic sample.

602
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,050
Group E?

603
00:27:30,710 --> 00:27:31,490
Exactly.

604
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,340
Their methods

605
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,730
are very similar to Group E's
from three years ago.

606
00:27:36,470 --> 00:27:38,250
And your first thought

607
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:39,940
was to use me as bait?

608
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:41,450
Yes.

609
00:27:42,030 --> 00:27:43,660
Once I'd made that judgment,

610
00:27:43,710 --> 00:27:45,250
I decided to play along

611
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:48,010
and set a trap for the handler

612
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,180
with the genetic samples.

613
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,730
We had to catch the gold smugglers, too.

614
00:27:52,750 --> 00:27:53,820
That was going to tie up

615
00:27:53,990 --> 00:27:55,340
a lot of manpower.

616
00:27:55,790 --> 00:27:56,580
You

617
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,940
have zero field experience

618
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:59,100
dealing with mules.

619
00:27:59,470 --> 00:28:01,530
So you were the perfect bait.

620
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:03,420
See?

621
00:28:03,470 --> 00:28:05,010
Wasn't that exactly what I said?

622
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,290
Cong used the fact
that Zhang Yu was a rookie

623
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,530
to make the handler take the bait.

624
00:28:09,070 --> 00:28:10,210
Not entirely.

625
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:12,210
I was observing Zhang Yu

626
00:28:12,230 --> 00:28:12,940
yesterday.

627
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:13,970
She learns quickly

628
00:28:13,990 --> 00:28:15,530
and adapts quickly.

629
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,210
To be honest,

630
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:19,970
I was still a little worried.

631
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:21,860
I was worried you'd be too composed.

632
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:24,290
So before the pre-shift meeting,

633
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:25,530
I left you all some time.

634
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:28,140
I was hoping you guys
could teach her a few tricks.

635
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:30,770
A small genetic sample container
like this

636
00:28:30,790 --> 00:28:31,770
can only be opened

637
00:28:31,790 --> 00:28:33,580
in a special
genetic testing identification chamber.

638
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,420
It's impossible to crack.

639
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:35,970
If we ever come across one,

640
00:28:35,990 --> 00:28:36,750
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
we'll definitely

641
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:37,490
[Blood Genetic Sample Container]
check that bag.

642
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:39,900
If a suspect intends
to carry one out through customs…

643
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,100
That means

644
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,900
they'll disguise the container

645
00:28:43,990 --> 00:28:46,690
and hide it in their carry-on items.

646
00:28:46,990 --> 00:28:48,940
Also, I taught her

647
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:51,690
a multi-factor probability approach.

648
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,860
Think from the smugglers' point of view.

649
00:28:54,070 --> 00:28:55,180
If you were them,

650
00:28:55,230 --> 00:28:56,620
what kind of handler would you want?

651
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:57,970
Then, one more angle.

652
00:28:58,030 --> 00:28:59,690
If you were the handler,

653
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:01,620
how would you deal
with being short-handed?

654
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:04,490
I'd find a partner.

655
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,770
Knowing too much too soon

656
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,210
can backfire.

657
00:29:09,070 --> 00:29:10,620
She learned a lot of methods,

658
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,100
but she didn't know how to use them.

659
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:14,770
So what the handler saw was her panic

660
00:29:14,790 --> 00:29:17,250
as she was overwhelmed
by too much information.

661
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:18,180
Nice.

662
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,970
Cong, you sneaky fox.

663
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,860
You worked all of us into your plan.

664
00:29:23,550 --> 00:29:24,660
Zhang Yu, see that?

665
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,860
That's your mentor.

666
00:29:26,550 --> 00:29:28,050
He can turn using people
into an art form.

667
00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:29,180
You'd better learn well.

668
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:31,450
To come up with a surefire plan

669
00:29:31,470 --> 00:29:33,140
that fast

670
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:34,490
and actually pull it off.

671
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:36,380
That's exactly why he's my mentor.

672
00:29:38,710 --> 00:29:40,580
Just don't blame me
for putting you out there.

673
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,180
And don't rush

674
00:29:42,200 --> 00:29:42,970
the mentor thing.

675
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:43,770
We'll talk about it later.

676
00:29:45,270 --> 00:29:46,210
Just talk about it right now.

677
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:47,690
It's okay.

678
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:50,010
My mentor's testing me.

679
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,820
I know I'll pass.

680
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:53,860
But Cong, I've got to say this.

681
00:29:53,990 --> 00:29:55,770
You're a mentor now.

682
00:29:56,310 --> 00:29:58,140
You need to look out for your trainee.

683
00:29:58,470 --> 00:29:59,420
Just leave

684
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:01,730
this decoy-and-bait business

685
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:02,820
to us old-timers in the future.

686
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:07,420
Today's the Mid-Autumn Festival.

687
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,690
Everyone, go home and get some rest.

688
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:10,620
Hey, don't leave yet.

689
00:30:10,710 --> 00:30:11,900
What's the rush?

690
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,940
It's still morning.

691
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,100
Zhang Yu officially joined

692
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:16,100
Passenger Inspection Section I today.

693
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:18,210
We should throw her a welcome dinner.

694
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:19,580
- Right? - Can't make it.

695
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:22,010
We finally get two days off
for the holiday.

696
00:30:22,030 --> 00:30:23,180
I promised Feng Ning

697
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,730
I'd take the kid to see her grandma.

698
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,450
You really need to spend time with her.

699
00:30:27,470 --> 00:30:28,210
I'm telling you,

700
00:30:28,230 --> 00:30:29,940
I haven't seen her smile once

701
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,180
since you two got married.

702
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,490
She doesn't have to smile for you.

703
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,100
That's true.

704
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:38,490
Smiling for you is enough.

705
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:40,970
But

706
00:30:40,990 --> 00:30:43,210
my situation isn't much better than his.

707
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:45,490
You all know Bing and I
both work for Customs.

708
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:48,530
We spend more time at work than at home.

709
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:50,620
And our parents
are pushing us to have a kid.

710
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:51,940
I don't really have a lot of time.

711
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:52,620
Right?

712
00:30:53,470 --> 00:30:54,580
So I'll probably have to leave, too.

713
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,900
Zhang Yu, I owe you a meal.

714
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,140
I'll make it up to you.

715
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:59,820
You young folks,
don't follow my example.

716
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:00,820
- Okay. - Okay.

717
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:04,210
Mr. Guo, you don't have
a family to worry about.

718
00:31:04,230 --> 00:31:05,690
You're kind of young, I'd say.

719
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:06,490
Join us?

720
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:07,690
I've got something today.

721
00:31:08,270 --> 00:31:10,530
You guys organize a dinner
to welcome Zhang Yu.

722
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:11,530
Put the bill on me.

723
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:13,250
Come on, Mr. Guo.

724
00:31:13,270 --> 00:31:14,970
Zhang Yu is practically your trainee!

725
00:31:14,990 --> 00:31:16,100
I do have something to handle.

726
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:17,820
You always do.

727
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,210
Yan Bowen!

728
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,140
Throw Zhang Yu a welcome party.

729
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,340
And help her tidy up her dorm.

730
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:25,970
Let's go!

731
00:31:28,070 --> 00:31:30,100
Time to eat!

732
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:33,180
Here, a big bowl for my son.

733
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:34,730
- Here. - Thanks, Mom.

734
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:35,580
Careful, it's hot.

735
00:31:37,550 --> 00:31:38,100
Son.

736
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:39,490
Even Ms. Zhang downstairs

737
00:31:39,510 --> 00:31:41,420
saw that video of you,

738
00:31:42,030 --> 00:31:43,770
China's Most Handsome Customs Officer.

739
00:31:43,790 --> 00:31:45,340
She just called me about it.

740
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,050
You got filmed like that.

741
00:31:49,310 --> 00:31:50,970
What if the bad guys see it?

742
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,420
Doesn't Customs do anything about that?

743
00:31:53,030 --> 00:31:54,340
It's the age of social media.

744
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,820
Everyone has a phone.
How can we stop it?

745
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,660
Can't control all of it.

746
00:31:57,680 --> 00:31:58,660
That won't do.

747
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,620
It's too dangerous.

748
00:32:01,030 --> 00:32:02,180
Did you forget your mentor…?

749
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:02,900
Mom.

750
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,730
He was a special case.

751
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,050
There are plenty of people in Customs.

752
00:32:08,070 --> 00:32:09,180
Everyone's fine.

753
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:11,010
Besides, nobody will care

754
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:12,420
about that video in a little while.

755
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:14,450
Just make sure

756
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,380
you take care of yourself.

757
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,690
Go see Mr. Xiang
after you finish your meal.

758
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:21,010
There are freshly made beef meatballs
in the fridge.

759
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:22,010
Bring him some.

760
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:23,210
Okay.

761
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:25,490
I heard he got some new equipment.

762
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:26,180
I'll drop by and take a look.

763
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:35,530
Yu.

764
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:36,690
What…?

765
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:38,140
What is this?

766
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:39,580
Heavy as hell.

767
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,860
It's all books.

768
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:44,620
I don't have much luggage. Just books.

769
00:32:45,030 --> 00:32:46,140
Thanks for the help.

770
00:32:47,070 --> 00:32:48,820
Isn't a tablet better?

771
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:50,380
One tablet in hand,

772
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:51,690
and you're good to go anywhere.

773
00:32:51,750 --> 00:32:52,620
Yan Bowen,

774
00:32:52,710 --> 00:32:54,530
stop talking and get to work.

775
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,100
Not following your master's example now?

776
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:57,210
Oh my.

777
00:32:57,750 --> 00:32:58,530
Oh my goodness.

778
00:33:06,710 --> 00:33:08,770
He really does work hard.

779
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:11,380
You don't have to turn into your mentor.

780
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:14,010
You and Deng are pretty different.

781
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:15,690
People

782
00:33:15,710 --> 00:33:17,580
who spend a lot of time together
start to grow alike.

783
00:33:18,070 --> 00:33:20,900
Maybe one day my mentor will become

784
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,940
as lively and cheerful as I am.

785
00:33:28,470 --> 00:33:29,180
That's everything, right?

786
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:29,620
Oh…

787
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:31,050
That's all of it.

788
00:33:31,070 --> 00:33:31,860
Thanks.

789
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:33,050
Everything

790
00:33:33,750 --> 00:33:34,860
is here.

791
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:36,340
Thanks.

792
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,140
No problem.

793
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:38,970
You've got two beds here.

794
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,010
I'll move this one out for you later.

795
00:33:41,030 --> 00:33:41,820
It's taking up space.

796
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,690
Leave it. Just keep it there.

797
00:33:44,030 --> 00:33:45,530
Yu doesn't have much stuff anyway.

798
00:33:45,750 --> 00:33:48,290
Maybe someday
I won't feel like going home,

799
00:33:48,310 --> 00:33:49,450
and I'll crash here with you.

800
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:50,250
Right.

801
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:53,010
And if someone bullies you or something,

802
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:55,100
you can come over for a drink and vent.

803
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:57,250
Not happening. Who'd dare bully me?

804
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:58,660
True.

805
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:01,580
Yan Bowen,

806
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:03,450
did you order the hot pot?

807
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:04,490
Yes.

808
00:34:04,790 --> 00:34:06,690
You didn't have it delivered
to Yu's room, did you?

809
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,820
That smell will linger for days.

810
00:34:10,670 --> 00:34:11,900
I had it delivered to my room.

811
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:19,650
He's changing the address now.

812
00:34:19,990 --> 00:34:21,050
I knew he wouldn't think of it.

813
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:27,220
What do you think of my Zenit?

814
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:28,380
Do I need to get you a set sometime?

815
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:32,610
I wouldn't dare.

816
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:33,380
You know,

817
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,610
we have rules and regulations.

818
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,970
I can't accept a gift that expensive.

819
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,330
I'll work hard,

820
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,970
earn my own money,

821
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:41,970
and buy one myself.

822
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:42,850
Come on.

823
00:34:42,870 --> 00:34:44,300
What's wrong with spending my money?

824
00:34:44,830 --> 00:34:46,010
My money is your money.

825
00:34:46,030 --> 00:34:47,140
What can anyone say?

826
00:34:48,590 --> 00:34:49,410
I'm telling you,

827
00:34:49,750 --> 00:34:52,540
if you had taken over the company,

828
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,810
maybe I'd be spending your money by now.

829
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:56,420
This company

830
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:59,060
was built by your father and me.

831
00:34:59,350 --> 00:35:00,810
It's our life's work.

832
00:35:02,830 --> 00:35:04,850
Now you're leaving it with no successor.

833
00:35:04,870 --> 00:35:06,010
How am I supposed

834
00:35:06,030 --> 00:35:07,900
to explain this to your late father?

835
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:09,900
Here we go again.

836
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,420
I did try, didn't I?

837
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:13,020
Maybe it's just fate.

838
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:17,570
The truth is, I'm more interested
in people than money.

839
00:35:18,630 --> 00:35:19,700
And whose fault is that?

840
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,290
If you hadn't taught me photography

841
00:35:21,310 --> 00:35:23,290
and observation skills,

842
00:35:23,550 --> 00:35:25,380
would my mentor ever
have spotted me right away?

843
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:27,900
Come on, guys.

844
00:35:28,990 --> 00:35:30,700
Let's welcome Zhang Yu

845
